ctions as the underlying cause. This relationship underscores the diverse ways in which physical health issues can lead to mental disorders, emphasizing the need for tailored treatment approaches based on the specific cause of the condition. [Data: Relationships (556)]\n\n## Lipowski's theory of diffuse brain energy alteration\n\nLipowski, a key researcher in this community, proposed the theory of diffuse brain energy alteration as a common pathophysiological change in mental disorders due to physical diseases. This theory is central to understanding the mechanisms underlying these conditions, providing a framework for how physical health issues can lead to psychiatric symptoms. Lipowski's work highlights the importance of considering brain energy changes in the diagnosis and treatment of these disorders, further emphasizing the need for a holistic approach to patient care. [Data: Entities (1340), Relationships (1501)]\n\n## Holistic treatment approach in general hospital settings\n\nThe management of 躯体疾病所致精神障碍 typically occurs within general hospital settings, where both the physical and mental health aspects of the patient can be addressed concurrently. This approach is crucial for effectively treating these conditions, as it allows for the simultaneous management of the underlying physical illness and its psychiatric manifestations. The emphasis on holistic treatment underscores the importance of integrating physical and mental health care to achieve optimal patient outcomes. [Data: Entities (461)]"], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-v3"}}}